@startuml c4-jotp-09b-graceful-shutdown
title JOTP - Graceful Shutdown Sequence

participant "Application\nMain" as Main
participant "RootSupervisor" as Root
participant "ChildSup1" as ChildSup1
participant "ChildSup2" as ChildSup2
participant "Workers" as Workers
participant "ProcessRegistry" as Registry
participant "VirtualThreads" as VT

Main ->> Root: shutdown()
note over Main
  Initiate graceful shutdown
end note
activate Root

Root ->> ChildSup1: stop()
activate ChildSup1
Root ->> ChildSup2: stop()
activate ChildSup2

par Child Shutdown
  ChildSup1 ->> Workers: stop all workers
  activate Workers
  note over Workers
    Send stop messages
    Wait for ack
  end note
  Workers ->> Workers: cleanup resources
  Workers -->> ChildSup1: all stopped
  deactivate Workers

and
  ChildSup2 ->> Workers: stop all workers
  Workers ->> Workers: cleanup
  Workers -->> ChildSup2: done
end

ChildSup1 -->> Root: stopped
deactivate ChildSup1

ChildSup2 -->> Root: stopped
deactivate ChildSup2

Root ->> Registry: unregister all
note over Registry
  Remove all process references
  Auto-deregister children
end note

Root ->> VT: shutdown thread pool
activate VT
note over VT
  Stop accepting new tasks
  Wait for running tasks
  Graceful termination
end note
VT -->> Root: done
deactivate VT

Root -->> Main: shutdown complete
deactivate Root

Main -->> Main: JVM can exit
note over Main
  All resources freed
  All threads stopped
  Clean shutdown
end note

@enduml
